# Rendering (ZeroLight-Framework)

Read `docs/rendering-assets-shaders.md` and @AGENTS.md before editing.

- `Renderer` is the facade — game code does not import `src/render/gpu/*`
- Pair GPU resource create/destroy; `errdefer` on partial init (register `deinit` first when taking by-value ownership)
- `SpriteBatch` consumes pre-sorted ordered streams — not a fallback sorter
- Do not hold swapchain acquisition across substantial CPU prep
- Per-frame render path: no avoidable allocation, string lookup, or hash-map dispatch
- Persist stable asset IDs; resolve to texture IDs at render-prep boundary only
- Hot/frame-adjacent paths: no logging in release (comptime-gate or omit)
